  "text": "The Kafka Connect REST API does NOT use URL-path-based v1/v2 versioning (e.g., /api/v1/connectors vs /api/v2/connectors). Instead, the 'v1' and 'v2' refer to the Connect group protocol versions (V0=eager, V1=incremental cooperative, V2=sessioned with KIP-507 internal request signing). The REST API resource handlers are: ConnectorsResource (@Path(\"/connectors\")) for the main public connector API, ConnectorPluginsResource (@Path(\"/connector-plugins\")), RootResource (@Path(\"/\")), InternalClusterResource/InternalConnectResource for inter-worker communication, all registered by ConnectRestServer. The version routing logic lives in ConnectProtocolCompatibility (maps V0/V1/V2 to EAGER/COMPATIBLE/SESSIONED), ConnectProtocol (V0 schemas), and IncrementalCooperativeConnectProtocol (V1/V2 schemas with extended assignments including revoked connectors/tasks and scheduled delay). Between V1 and V2, the assignment schema is structurally identical (same ASSIGNMENT_V1 schema), but V2 enables session key distribution for securing internal REST endpoints. The task status schema (ConnectorStateInfo.TaskState) includes state, worker_id, msg, version fields with trace conditionally included. The error response schema (ErrorMessage) contains error_code and message fields, mapped by ConnectExceptionMapper.",
